# Project Context

This is a **documentation project** built with **Fumadocs** - a modern documentation framework for Next.js.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Documentation**: Fumadocs (fumadocs-core, fumadocs-mdx, fumadocs-ui)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Content Format**: MDX (Markdown with React components)
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (preferred)

## Project Structure

### Content Collections

- `content/docs/` - Main documentation content (MDX files)
- `content/blog/` - Blog posts (MDX files)
- `content/fumadocs/` - Fumadocs-specific documentation (MDX files)

### Source Configuration

- `source.config.ts` - Defines content collections and metadata schemas
- `lib/source.ts` - Source loaders for each collection (docs, blog, fumadocs)

### Routes

- `app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` - Documentation pages
- `app/blog/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` - Blog pages
- `app/fumadocs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` - Fumadocs documentation pages
- `app/api/search/route.ts` - Search API endpoint

## Guidelines

### When working with content:

- All content is written in MDX format (`.mdx` files)
- Content files should follow Fumadocs frontmatter schema
- Use the collections defined in `source.config.ts`
- Respect the existing directory structure for content

### When modifying code:

- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use Fumadocs APIs and conventions
- Maintain the existing source loader patterns
- Keep layouts consistent with Fumadocs UI components

### When adding features:

- Leverage Fumadocs features (search, OG images, LLM text generation)
- Use Fumadocs UI components from `fumadocs-ui`
- Maintain consistency with existing documentation patterns

## Key Files

- `lib/source.ts` - Main source configuration and loaders
- `source.config.ts` - Content collection definitions
- `lib/layout.shared.tsx` - Shared layout options
- `mdx-components.tsx` - MDX component overrides

## Important Notes

- This is a **documentation project**, not a general web application
- All content should be written in MDX format
- Fumadocs handles routing and page generation automatically
- The project uses Fumadocs' built-in features for search, navigation, and metadata
- When suggesting changes, consider how they affect the documentation experience
